  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contracting obligations to Montana totaled $792M in FY2026 to date. Award activity reached 5,226 awards with an average award size of $151K, while obligations were down 30.9% year over year. Historical obligations show variability: FY21 totaled $691M, FY22 totaled $925M, FY23 totaled $1B, FY24 totaled $1.1B, and FY25 totaled $1.1B. The Department of Defense led buying in FY2026 to date with $303M in obligations, followed by the Department of Agriculture with $175M and the Department of Homeland Security with $133M. Contracting in construction and repair sectors dominated spending by industry: Commercial and Institutional Building Construction accounted for $114M and Electronic and Precision Equipment Repair and Maintenance accounted for $107M. Vendors concentrated a large share of obligations: S & K SECURITY GROUP LLC received $106M and ARCHER WESTERN FEDERAL JV received $58.8M. Other notable vendor awards included PAF ELECTRICAL, INC. at $57M and S & K AEROSPACE, LLC at $30M. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
