      },
      {
        "heading": "What are the dominant industries and vendors in Montana federal contracting?",
        "body": "Construction and equipment repair sectors lead industry obligations, with Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $114M and Electronic and Precision Equipment Repair and Maintenance at $107M. The largest vendors are S & K SECURITY GROUP LLC at $106M and ARCHER WESTERN FEDERAL JV at $58.8M, followed by PAF ELECTRICAL, INC. at $57M and S & K AEROSPACE, LLC at $30M."
